<h1>Transparen Corporation</h1>
<hr/>
<pre>
Transparen Corporation incorporated within Canada with offices physically
located in the province of British Columbia (BC), Canada.
Transparen Corporation provides services to businesses in Canada,
the United States (USA), the United Kingdom, and many other parts of the
world.  Transparen Corporation can accept credit card payments and can
deliver custom software anywhere that has Internet access.

Transparen Corporation makes use of a global network of support
professionals, including programmers in Canada, the United States, Russia,
and Ukraine.  Transparen's consultants are located in Canada and the
United States.

Transparen has several principle service areas, which include:
- Linux and Windows technical support
- Linux customization
- Technical Writing
- Custom Software Projects

Clients in India and Pakistan make use of Transparen's technical writing
services, while clients in Canada and the United States make use of
Transparen's Linux customization capabilities, or other custom software
projects.

Transparen's average project size is 12,000 USD, with some projects as
large as 100,000 USD, and some as small as 2,000 USD.

Transparen provides commercial Debian
support to clients requesting web or email servers for business
applications. Service is provide on-site or by remote methods, as
appropriate.

Transparen Corporation supports clients in their use of Debian to
replace Microsoft Windows domain controllers, where appropriate.

Transparen Corporation provides Linux customization services to
clients who wish to produce Debian-based kiosks for retail locations.

Transparen Corporation employs a computer running Debian as part of a
custom hard drive data recovery process.

Transparen Corporation supports Debian and uses Debian for desktop and
server functions, and supports commercial clients who use Debian.

Transparen can assist clients with scripting and decision
support tools that utilize the Debian system as an underlying technology.

Transparen can provide insights into how to use Debian to make a
wide variety of businesses more efficient and profitable.

Transparen uses computers with the Debian operating system in its research
into optimizing business processes and decision support processes.
